COVID-19: Dangote tests negative, announces initiative to combat corona virus Africa’s richest man Aliko Danogote, revealed on Sunday revealed that he tested negative for COVID-19. Dangote, who made this known in on twitter, also disclosed that he was leading a groups of private sector leaders to support government in combating Coronavirus. He said, “The COVID-19 pandemic has significantly disrupted modern society, affecting our collective health and well-being. “As a global citizen and business leader, I took the COVID-19 test and the result came back NEGATIVE. He said Coalition Against COVID-19  CACOVID-19 was an initiative of private sector leaders coming together to provide resource to combat Coronavirus. “CACOVID (Coalition Against COVID-19) is an initiative that I am leading with other private sector leaders & our common goal is to support ongoing Government initiatives with our resources in the fight against Covid-19. We are in this together & I am optimistic we will overcome,” Dangote stated.